00:00:42.030 --> 00:00:44.230
OK here's the setup. This is my dad's

00:00:44.250 --> 00:00:48.310
AK-47. First things first. The weapon is clear.

00:00:48.330 --> 00:00:52.340
So, on the back of this thing there's a little tab that the

00:00:52.360 --> 00:00:56.400
stock for the weapon, you can see it's captured right here, so all I've done

00:00:56.420 --> 00:01:00.430
is I've created the reciprocal of that out of metal. So we have that

00:01:00.450 --> 00:01:04.470
on this side, and on the other side we capture it with a J-bolt.

00:01:04.490 --> 00:01:08.510
So you can see, clicked in position.

00:01:08.530 --> 00:01:12.530
And here, captured with a J-bolt.

00:01:12.550 --> 00:01:16.560
If you don't know your way around an AK-47 it's pretty simple. You just take the top cover off,

00:01:16.580 --> 00:01:20.580
take this spring out, and then you can pull the bolt back. And when you pull the bolt back

00:01:20.600 --> 00:01:24.610
which is located right here you see this large piston. Now this piston is

00:01:24.630 --> 00:01:28.670
what operates the mechanism that re-chambers the next round. It's pretty simple the way these things

00:01:28.690 --> 00:01:32.680
work. As a bullet travels down the barrel, it passes

00:01:32.700 --> 00:01:36.700
a port right here, and this port allows gases to flow into a cylinder

00:01:36.720 --> 00:01:40.730
which drives this piston back, which moves the bolt and the

00:01:40.750 --> 00:01:44.770
bolt re-chambers another round out of the magazine. So here's the question. As the gas flows

00:01:44.790 --> 00:01:48.800
into the cylinder and begins pushing down this piston, what

00:01:48.820 --> 00:01:52.830
happens to all this water? My hypothesis is that it's going to slow the bolt down

00:01:52.850 --> 00:01:56.870
but we're gonna use the high speed footage to determine if this is correct. We have a

00:01:56.890 --> 00:02:00.890
little bolt cover here and we've painted the end of it white so that we can measure the velocity of it in

00:02:00.910 --> 00:02:04.910
a high speed video. First shot, air. As you can see here

00:02:04.930 --> 00:02:06.920
we're firing directly into this dirt burm.

