00:04:39.310 --> 00:04:41.930
So I've got two theories about why water is faster.

00:04:41.950 --> 00:04:45.940
Well if you think about it, if you have a round in the chamber you have a big column of water in front of it.

00:04:45.960 --> 00:04:49.980
So you have to accelerate all of that mass instead of just the mass of the bullet.

00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:54.020
That makes sense because you can look here and see that the primer's blown out, indicating

00:04:54.040 --> 00:04:58.050
that there's higher chamber pressure when we do that. That means that there's more force

00:04:58.070 --> 00:05:02.060
pushing on this piston. Also water is incompressible whereas air is compressible.

00:05:02.080 --> 00:05:06.110
That means that the pressure information gets to the piston faster. Alright

